If:

$$
A = \begin{pmatrix} 
1 & 2 \\ 
3 & 4 
\end{pmatrix}
$$

$$
T = \begin{pmatrix} 
2 & 0 \\ 
0 & 2 
\end{pmatrix}
$$

$$
S = \begin{pmatrix} 
1 & 1 \\ 
0 & 1 
\end{pmatrix}
$$

First, check that $$T$$ and $$S$$ are invertible:
- $$det(T) = 4 \neq 0$$
- $$det(S) = 1 \neq 0$$

Compute the inverses:

$$
T^{-1} = \begin{pmatrix} 
\frac{1}{2} & 0 \\ 
0 & \frac{1}{2} 
\end{pmatrix}
$$

Then, perform the transformation:

$$
A' = T^{-1}AS = \begin{pmatrix} 
\frac{1}{2} & 0 \\ 
0 & \frac{1}{2} 
\end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix} 
1 & 2 \\ 
3 & 4 
\end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix} 
1 & 1 \\ 
0 & 1 
\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 
0.5 & 1.5 \\ 
1.5 & 3.5 
\end{pmatrix}
$$
